# Secrets hygiene

Tokens for Paramify, GitLab, Okta, KnowBe4, Rippling, etc. flow through this code. Treat every value as radioactive.

## Hard rules

- **Never** log a secret value, include it in an error message, or render it on screen unless the operator explicitly unmasked it; even then, do not write it to a log file.
- `Store.List()` returns key names only; never values.
- Inputs masked by default in the Secrets screen. Toggle reveal is transient view-state, not persisted.
- Scrub `os.Environ()` before printing it anywhere (debug dumps, crash diagnostics).

## Storage backends

- `keychain.Store` (default for new installs) — `github.com/zalando/go-keyring`.
- `dotenv.Store` — back-compat read of an existing `.env` at the configured fetcher repo root. Mark as insecure in the UI when active.
- `memory.Store` — tests only; never persists.

Reads merge keychain first, dotenv fallback. Writes go to whichever backend the user picked at setup.

## Multi-instance keys

Stored as `paramify-fetcher/<service>/<instance>/<key>` in the keychain. Reconstructed into `<SERVICE>_<N>_*` env vars **at exec time** so the existing fetcher contract is preserved unchanged.

## Test snapshot rule

Any new test that exercises a secret path must assert that the value never appears in captured stdout/stderr or rendered view output.
